The paper discusses fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in computer science. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the societal impact of machine learning algorithms. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the definitions of fairness in machine learning. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another likely category as the paper studies the comprehension of fairness definitions by a non-technical audience. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of bias in machine learning on various areas such as medicine, hiring, and criminal justice.
